            "title": "Trump imposes 35% tariff on Canadian goods, 68 other nations face new trade war with tariffs ranging from 10% to 50%.",
            "id": "a98591a3-338d-463c-bb62-c7fcafb7cbab",
            "description": "President Trump has imposed new tariffs on 69 countries, escalating tensions over fentanyl, national security, and China. Tariffs range from 10% to 41%, with Canada facing a 35% tariff for allegedly failing to combat fentanyl flows. Brazil will face a 50% tariff, while India, Taiwan, and Switzerland among others face 20% to 39% tariffs. A baseline 10% tariff applies to countries not listed. Talks with India broke down over agriculture and Russian ties, leading to threats of further penalties. The move intensifies the global trade standoff.",
